    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Voluntary conformity of one’s life and conduct with the principles of morality and standards of right conduct, including abstention on moral grounds from wrong-doing or vice. The virtues vary by culture. In traditional western or Christian culture, they include faith, hope, charity, prudence, justice, temperance, courage, chastity, diligence, patience, and humility.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
